What  happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?
   It creates a .git file to keep meta data in
How is the staging area different from the working directory and repository? What value does it offer
   just a holding place so you can control what will be added to repository. Allows control
How can you use the staging area to make sure you have one commit per logical change?
     only add one file at a time to staging area that has logical change in it
What are some situations when branches would be helpful in keeping  your history organized? How would branches help.
  adding  new features that may not get used. Can decide to merge in later if it improves things. 
How do diagrams help you visualize the branch structure?
    allows you to see graphically how to get back and how to merge if needed.
    